"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126471","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-05-17","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) intends to undertake a public consultation on legal protections measures for personnel deployed on operations overseas, including a statutory presumption against prosecution of current or former personnel for alleged offences committed in the course of duty abroad more than 10 years previously. Prosecutions in such circumstances would not be considered to be in the public interest, except in “exceptional circumstances”. The presumption measure would not apply to historical alleged offences in Northern Ireland. The Secretary of State for Defence will continue to work with the Northern Ireland Secretary on the proposals for addressing Northern Ireland legacy issues. The MOD provides veterans, including those who served in Northern Ireland, who are subject to investigation and potential prosecution with legal, welfare and pastoral support.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","252557 ; 252559","2019-05-17T13:46:38.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126471/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126471/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-05-14","Veterans: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans she has to bring forward legislative proposals to protect veterans accused of historic allegations relating to service in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","254180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126472","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-05-20","<p>On 9 May, Government announced its commitment to fully fund the remediation of private sector high-rise residential blocks (above 18 metres) with unsafe Aluminium Composite Material cladding, except where a warranty claim has been accepted. This will allow remediation to happen quickly. We continue to put pressure on building owners and developers to make their buildings permanently safe as swiftly as possible.</p><p>We are not expecting any further applications from social sector building owners but we will still accept applications from any building owners who require funding.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2019-05-20T14:50:00.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126472/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126472/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-05-14","High Rise Flats: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will put in place a deadline by which ACM cladding will have been removed from (a) private and (b) social housing blocks.","false","Biography information for Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","Slough","Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","254265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126473","Department for International Development","false","2019-05-20","<p>The Withdrawal Agreement ensures that UK based organisations will be able to bid for funding, participate in and lead consortia and otherwise implement as normal EU development programmes that are approved before December 2020 until they complete. Furthermore, we are clear that any future UK financial contribution to the EU would require eligibility for UK entities to bid for and implement programmes where the UK funds. We regularly consult NGOs regarding their concerns to ensure we can support our world-class development sector. I therefore urge the Hon. Gentleman to support the Withdrawal Agreement.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2019-05-20T16:07:24.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126473/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126473/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-05-14","Non-governmental Organisations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps he is taking to ensure that NGOs are able to continue their work unaffected by the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","Slough","Mr Tanmanjeet Singh Dhesi","254266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126474","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-05-22","<p>Building owners are responsible for ensuring residents are informed of fire safety issues in their buildings. We are engaging with building owners, managing agents, local authorities and others to ensure that remediation happens as quickly as possible, and that interim safety measures are in place in all buildings until the cladding is replaced.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2019-05-22T12:54:52.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126474/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126474/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-05-14","Buildings: Insulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 9 May 2019 to Question 249214 on Buildings: Insulation, what evidence he has received that all residents have been informed of the inclusion of their residences in his Department's Building Safety Programme monthly data release.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","254136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126475","Department for Transport","false","2019-05-20","<p>The Intercity Express Programme technical specification includes a requirement that the IEP Trains be capable of providing a range of catering services, from which specific catering services and combinations may be selected. The IEP train also has a flexible design that allows changes to the catering provision in response to future requirements. The Great Western Intercity Express trains comply with all relevant catering requirements and the Department has no plans to make any changes to the Great Western IET fleet.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2019-05-20T15:24:32.687Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126475/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126475/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-05-14","Great Western Railway Line: Catering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has for the alteration of Great Western Intercity Express trains so that they comply with section 6.2.6 of the Intercity Express Programme technical specification on catering provision.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","254217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126476","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-05-20","<p>The hearing has been listed by the Court on a private and confidential basis. The Ministry of Defence is not a party to these proceedings and there will be no public or third-party access to the hearing.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2019-05-20T16:41:03.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126476/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126476/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-05-14","Iran: International Military Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 9 May 2019 to Question 251360 on Iran: International Military Services, for what reason she is not at liberty to disclose the date.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","254250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126477","Department for Transport","false","2019-05-20","<p>Abellio’s bid contained assurances regarding the availability, capability and characteristics of the rolling stock that will be introduced on the Midland Mainline. With regard to the procurement of these trains, I refer the Honourable member to the answer given on 8 May [249827].</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2019-05-20T15:00:24.483Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126477/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126477/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-05-14","East Midlands Rail Franchise: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 23 April 2019 to Question 244025 and the Answer of 8 May 2019 249827 on East Midlands Rail Franchise: Rolling Stock , what assurances he has received from the train operator as to which type of diesel trains will replace the current fleet on Midland Main Line intercity services; and where those trains will be procured from.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","254132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126478","Department for Transport","false","2019-05-20","<p>Network Rail, who produce industry performance data, may hold the information requested.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2019-05-20T15:03:27.953Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126478/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126478/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-05-14","Railways: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 8 May 2019 to Question 249824 on Railways: Sheffield, which organisation holds the information requested.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","254133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126479","Department for Transport","false","2019-05-20","<p>The Department holds various punctuality reports relating to the main industry punctuality measures that have been used historically, the Public Performance Measure and Cancellations and Significant Lateness. This information is held at train operator level, and down to the level of groups of services run by an operator. We do not hold data for individual routes themselves.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2019-05-20T15:05:57.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126479/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126479/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-05-14","Railways: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 8 May 2019 to Question 249824 on Railways: Sheffield, what information his Department holds on train punctuality.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","254134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126480","Department for International Trade","false","2019-05-20","<p>I refer the Hon. Member for Sheffield South East to the answer I gave to the Hon. Member for Newcastle-under-Lyme on 8 April 2019, UIN: 239902/239903/239904.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2019-05-20T13:50:32.16Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126480/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126480/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-05-14","Saudi Arabia: Sports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what representations he has made to the Saudi Government on reports that live sports broadcasting rights are allegedly being stolen in that country.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","254135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126481","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-05-20","<p>The role of the Victims’ Commissioner is greatly valued across the justice system and the Government welcomes the recent appointment of Dame Vera Baird QC to the role.</p><p> </p><p>Dame Vera’s appointment was made in line with the Governance Code for Public Appointments which prescribes that all public appointments should be governed by the principle of appointment on merit. An assessment of the costs of a by-election was not factored into the appointment process.</p><p> </p><p><em>A Police and Crime Commissioner by-election will be run by a statutorily independent Returning Officer and will be funded out of the </em><em>Consolidated Fund</em><em>. </em></p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2019-05-20T15:23:57.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126481/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126481/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-05-14","Northumbria Police and Crime Commissioner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the appointment of Vera Baird as Victims' Commissioner, (a) what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of holding a by-election for a new Northumbria Police and Crime Commissioner; and (b) whether an assessment was made of that cost as part of that appointment process.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","254270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126482","Treasury","false","2019-05-20","<p>I thank the honourable member for Glasgow North for his question, and refer him to my answer of 14 November to PQ UIN 189731.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2019-05-20T15:52:43.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126482/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126482/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-05-14","Debts: Developing Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish a response to Early Day Motion 158 on Transparency of developing country debts.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","254221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126483","Treasury","false","2019-05-21","<p>This government remains clear in its support for consumers, pubs and breweries, and we have taken action to this end – ensuring the price of a pint of beer is 14p is lower than it otherwise would have been since ending the beer duty escalator in 2013.</p><p> </p><p>All taxes are kept under review and the impact of a change to beer duty is considered at each fiscal event, including its effect on pubs and the wider economy.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2019-05-21T07:44:16.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126483/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126483/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-05-14","Beer: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will reduce beer duty in Budget 2019.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","254273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126484","Treasury","false","2019-05-20","<p>Since the Check, Challenge, Appeal system was introduced, the Valuation Office Agency (VOA) has received 82,300 Checks, 87% of which have been resolved. The Non-Domestic Rating (Alteration of Lists and Appeals) (England) (Amendment) Regulations 2017 allow for up to 12 months to complete a Check unless an extension is agreed. If an extension is not agreed the customer has the right to progress to Challenge. Some cases are more complex than others and this can affect the time taken to resolve them.</p><p> </p><p>As at 31 March 2019, the average time taken by the VOA to complete a Check is 54 calendar days.</p><p> </p><p>Of the Checks outstanding;</p><p>(a) 1,504 have been outstanding for more than three months;</p><p>(b) 757 have been outstanding for more than six months; and</p><p>(c) Fewer than five have been outstanding for over 12 months. Statistical disclosure guidelines mean the precise figure is too small to publish.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the longest time taken to complete a Check cannot be provided due to the possibility of breaching disclosure guidelines.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","254213 ; 254214","2019-05-20T14:51:57.477Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126484/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126484/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1126484/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-05-14","Non-Domestic Rates: Valuation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average time taken by the Valuation Office Agency is to complete a business rateable value check.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","254212"
